			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I just want to express that I'm rather sad that apparently there are some people who get information that is kept from the communities. Maybe this is a rant, mods please decide.
<br />

<br />
Yesterday (or earlier, I'm not sure) there appeared a thread with a quote from Rytan which listed some mitigation comparisons for different pets and showed some possible improvements.
<br />

<br />
Apparently this quote was taken from a private message. Now I really have to ask, why do some people have private communication with developers and get information that is HIGHLY interesting to our class as a whole?
<br />

<br />
And when this information is "leaked" out to others, the posts get deleted. Are we not worthy to get the same information? Why do some people get special treatment and receive such information before the rest?
<br />

<br />
Rytan asked for feedback in that thread, I am not sure if he expected it to be passed on to the class boards or if he was just asking the single person he was communicating with. But ESPECIALLY on this topic I would rather have information as early as possible so I can post some feedback BEFORE changes are implemented.
<br />

