				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think the point to keep in mind is that Rytan originally came to this board promising greatly improved communication. I assumed that he meant with mages in general, now I'm guessing that he only meant with an "elite" group of testers.
<br />

<br />
Proposed changes should be placed before the community <span style="font-style: italic">before</span> they go live, not after. We all know it can take years to get the dev's to participate in balancing discussions, and for the majority of the community to be shut out of the process is flat out wrong IMHO. Personally, I don't care if magician changes make it into the next patch. I do care that we get a chance to test these proposed changes ourselves, <span style="font-weight: bold">before</span> the devs move on to other projects. My hope is that they focus on getting things <span style="font-style: italic">right</span>, not just on getting things done. The easiest way to ensure that this will happen is to include more of the community in that discussion.
<br />

<br />
PS. This isn't a plea for the mods to ignore an NDA, its more of a plea for the dev's to include a wider range of people, and hopefully the entire community in this process.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1002541&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Naladini Dreamfyre</a>
<br />
Arch Mage of 63 Seasons - <a href="http://www.stormhammer.org/forums" target="_blank" class="postlink">Stormhammer</a>
