				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">That post from Rytan is spreading like wildfire among other class boards, so it's extremely hard to just place blame.  Most of the people that are posting it are clueless to the fact it may or may not have been a post on the dev boards.  Not even we know for sure if that is the case, we're only taking a potluck guess and agreeing.  As far as "reporting" IP's and such to Sony, that's the only part I think was wrong.  These boards exist to share information, so it is hard to quantify whether or not something is within the bounds of the NDA that Sony has.  We don't know this.  Rather than report the IP's of the random soul that thinks they are just sharing common information, tell Sony this stuff is getting spread and let them do their thing.  Threatening every informative post on a board in which information is meant to be shared only stems the desire for someone to share anything.  If the post is indeed a breach and may threaten the livelyhood of these boards, simply remove it and warn the folks that posted it why.  If they throw a big fit or continue posting supposed "L337" info, then take actions to ban them.  No need to make a big snafu out of everything <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062" taret=_blank>Sage Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a>
