				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The whole thing seems rather adolescent to me. 
<br />

<br />
Sure the natural - and seemingly eaiser - thing for SOE to do is to work things out on their own and run it by a select few.  Too bad their not more creative. Having an open, honest discussion with the player base is far better approach. Yes, you will not satisfy everyone. Yes, there will be flames, disagreement, etc. Yes, not everyone will get what they want. But what will result are some solutions the majority of the mage community will support.
<br />

<br />
This idea that some are "in the know" and some aren't ultimately backfires, as it clearly has.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
